# Bug Bounty & Red Team — Tools Command Reference (Part 2 — Advanced)

> Continuation of Part 1. Covers XSS/param discovery, secrets scanning, API testing, cloud recon, request smuggling, SSTI/SSRF, screenshotting, hash cracking, and Active Directory / lateral movement tools (OSCP track).
> ⚠️ AD/lateral-movement tools are for authorized labs (HTB, TryHackMe, home lab) — NOT for bug bounty targets unless explicitly in scope.

---

## 1. XSS Discovery

### dalfox
```bash
dalfox url https://target.com/page?param=test
dalfox file urls.txt -o dalfox_results.txt
echo "https://target.com/page?q=test" | dalfox pipe
```

### XSStrike
```bash
python3 xsstrike.py -u "https://target.com/page?param=test"
python3 xsstrike.py -u "https://target.com/page?param=test" --crawl
```

---

## 2. Parameter Discovery

### Arjun
```bash
arjun -u https://target.com/page
arjun -u https://target.com/page -m POST
arjun -i urls.txt -o params_found.txt
```

### ParamSpider
```bash
python3 paramspider.py -d target.com -o params.txt
```

### x8
```bash
x8 -u https://target.com/page -w wordlist.txt
```

